Diabetes Mellitus (DM) tipe 2, menurut American Diabetes Association (ADA) adalah kumpulan gejala yang ditandai oleh hiperglikemia akibat defek pada kerja insulin (resistensi insulin) dan sekresi insulin atau kedua-duanya. Berdasarkan Riset Kesehatan Dasar (Riskesdas) tahun 2013, terjadi peningkatan dari 1,1% (2007) menjadi 2,1% (2013)

Gejala khasnya, yaitu :
1. Polidipsi (selalu merasa haus)
2. Polifagia (lebih sering makan)
3. Poliuri (sering kencing) 
4 Penurunan berat badan yang tidak jelas sebabnya

Mari sama-sama hambat terjadinya Diabetes Mellitus (DM) tipe 2, dengan:
1. Mengecek secara berkala tekanan darah & kolestrol
2. Mengatur Berat Badan tetap ideal & konsumsi sayur dan buah setiap hari
3. Aktifitas fisik, seperti berjalan kaki paling tidak 150 menit per minggu
4. Berhenti merokok

Rammang-rammang berada di desa Salenrang, Kecamatan Bontoa, Kabupaten Maros, Provinsi Sulawesi Selatan, Indonesia.
Kemarin, saya menempuh sekitar dua 2 jam perjalanan dengan kendaraan roda empat dari Kota Makassar. Nama Rammang-rammang artinya "kabut" atau "awan". Menurut cerita penduduk sekitar, tempat ini diberi nama Rammang-rammang karna kabut atau awan yang selalu turun dipagi hari atau ketika hujan.

Saat-saat menakjubkan ketika saya menjelajahi Sungai Pute yang mengantarai pepohan Nipah disebelah kiri-kanan dengan kapal untuk pertama kalinya dan kemudian sampai di Desa Berua. Pesona alam yang masih hijau dan udara segar membuat pikiran melupakan sejenak penat hiruk pikuk kehidupan sehari-hari.

[WORLD LUPUS DAY 2017]
Lupus is serious, life-altering, and potentially fatal disease that deserves more understanding and support. It is more pervasive and severe than people think, and has a devastating impact that the public doesn't realize. In fact, research shows that a staggering two-thirds of the public knows little or nothing about lupus. While lupus knows no boundaries, knowing all you can about lupus can help control its impact.

I, Valen, am joining this campaign in order to encourage all people of the world to join #InFlareNotDespair campaign to understand more about lupus and help those affected by lupus to get more attention. Whatever you decide to do on this day, make sure you help make the lives of those with lupus a little bit better.

February 22nd, and we are 2 days away to International STAND Up for Bullying Day. As we commemmorate our special day, AMSA-Unhas would like you to share this post along with your photo with hand gesture above, showing you are with us in STAND UP for Bullying.

There is a difference between be honest and truthful versus being mean and hurtful. Bullying can happen in any form. It can happen face to face and it can happen in the cyber world. There are things that you can do to keep yourself and others safe.

Stop and think before you say or do something that could hurt someone else
Treat everyone with respect
Acknowledge that everyone is different, not better or worse.Just different
Notice if any bullying happen around you.
Do not stay still and start to Do something to help them
Use your heart everytime you decide to do something
Protect the vulnerable and do care for those in need
